text: The municipalities of Vietnam are cities in Vietnam that have the same government status as a province. Vietnam has 57 provinces and 6 municipalities. The municipalities are Hanoi (Vietnam's capital), Ho Chi Minh City (Vietnam's most populated city), Haiphong, Cantho, Huáº¿, and Danang. Each of these cities are also the six most populated cities in Vietnam. Category:Geography of Vietnam
